Is it just me...<br>
___________________________<br>
<br>
That's the understatement of the year. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Nobody seems happy.  There have been a lot of posts about magician DPS compared to other classes and I understand that in a grouping/raid situation.  As a soloist, the biggest thing I could get would be some kind of a root/quick escape spell which I doubt will ever happen.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualladdim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/02 11:34:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New Spells</span><hr size=1> Actually, I used to think how other class are out nuking us and out healing us, etc etc. But now that I stopped and look at our class from a 3rd person perspective I realize how powerful and needed our mage class is. We can summon focus items, haste items, ultravision necklace, armor for our pets, resist items, mod rods, and soon gate necklace as well as proccing weapons (that can be used by pets). And our most important spell: Call of the Hero. Can any other class do that? It's all unique to our mage class and its something none may take away. <p><p align="center"><a
href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150542"
target="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150542"><img
src="http://www.animearki.com/anniemei/alladdim.jpg" border="0"
width="595" height="164"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaisblackfingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/02 11:53:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New Spells</span><hr size=1> Aye alla, I hear that.  We really do rock everyone's world, I think maybe necros have an advantage (past the person behind the keys who makes all the difference) on us in duels just 'cuz they can fear our pet and we can't fear theirs.<br>
<br>
And we are a great class to have in a group.  So great in fact that people are often shocked.  I think that's the real problem-mages get no love =(<br>
<br>
Ought we be doing more?  I think so.  I started my mage back when people still thought it was funny to take a druid as a nuker over a mage.  Back (ever so long ago) when rogues would actually listen to mages and learn to time backstabs on air-pet stuns.  Rogues used to be smart enough to make a mage-rogue group viable- even kickass.<br>
<br>
But it's more important for people to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> know</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that mages rule.  I haven't been asked for a coldstone in 20some levels, and only get asked for focus as toys (granted I don't have the full final circle of focus items yet).<br>
<br>
The other thing is that the things we are needed for are taken for granted.  Nobody dies because the mod-rod didn't come through in time for the heal.  They die because the cleric didn't heal fast enough.  Even though it may be the mod-rod's fault.  People notice a good cleric when the heal comes in just right.  People don't notice a good mage who balances rodding just right to keep the cleric up but still saves the day with a nicely timed nuke.  No mage lovin.<br>
<br>
That and the proccing weapons.  I got SoR a couple of days before the (n-word deleted to keep the flames down) and have always wanted it back.  But that's just a personal thing.  Objectively proccing weapons aren't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> needed</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Just highly, highly (for me) desired.  Like druids desire heals.  I'm done now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utangting.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/02 1:39:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Proccing weapons</span><hr size=1> It would have been nice to get the proccing weapons at a lower level - I remember lvl 38 still using those lvl 34 pets was brutal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells>Spells</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START B